<content type="application/x.deki0805+xml" title="separator"><body xmlns:eval="http://mindtouch.com/2007/dekiscript">
<div class="noinclude"><span class="script">template.XULRefElem()</span></div>
<p>Creates a small separating gap between elements. This type of separator should be used to separate parts of a dialog. It doesn't draw a bar visually, but is just a small space. It is functionally equivalent to a <span class="script">template.XULElem("spacer")</span> except it defaults to a small size (usually 1.5 ems).</p>
<dl><dt> Attributes </dt><dd> <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("a-", "separator.orient", "orient")</span> </dd></dl> <dl><dt> Style classes </dt><dd> <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("s-", "groove")</span>, <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("s-", "groove-thin")</span>, <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("s-", "thin")</span> </dd></dl>
<h3 name="Examples">Examples</h3>
<pre>&lt;separator class="groove-thin"/&gt;
</pre>
<h3 name="Attributes">Attributes</h3>
<p><span class="script">template.XULAttrInc("separator.orient")</span> <span class="script">template.XULAttrInheritedWide()</span></p>
<h3 name="Properties">Properties</h3>
<p><span class="script">template.XULPropInheritedWide()</span></p>
<h3 name="Methods">Methods</h3>
<p><span class="script">template.XULMethInheritedWide()</span></p>
<h3 name="Style_classes">Style classes</h3>
<p>The following classes may be used to style the element. These classes should be used instead of changing the style of the element directly since they will fit more naturally with the user's selected theme.</p>
<p><span class="script">template.XULStyleInc("groove")</span> <span class="script">template.XULStyleInc("groove-thin")</span> <span class="script">template.XULStyleInc("thin")</span></p>
<h3 name="Related">Related</h3>
<dl><dt>Elements </dt><dd><span class="script">template.XULElem("spacer")</span>, <span class="script">template.XULElem("splitter")</span>, <span class="script">template.XULElem("menuseparator")</span>, <span class="script">template.XULElem("toolbarseparator")</span>, <span class="script">template.XULElem("treeseparator")</span>. </dd></dl>

